name: Nexosis.Api.Sessions

aliases.name: ForecastSessionRequest
aliases.comment:
Details used to Forecast using time series algorithms. `startDate` and `endDate` is the date range that should be forecasted.
`resultInterval` is the time interval at which the forecast should be made.
aliases.type: { name : Maybe.Maybe String , dataSourceName : Nexosis.Types.DataSet.DataSetName , columns : List Nexosis.Types.Columns.ColumnMetadata , missingValues : List String , dates : { startDate : Time.ZonedDateTime.ZonedDateTime , endDate : Time.ZonedDateTime.ZonedDateTime } , resultInterval : Nexosis.Types.Session.ResultInterval }

aliases.name: ImpactSessionRequest
aliases.comment:
Details used to determine Impact of an event using time series algorithms. `startDate` and `endDate` is the date range that should be measured for Impact.
`resultInterval` is the time interval at which the Impact should be made. `eventName` is a description name to help identify what impact is being measured in the date range.
aliases.type: { name : Maybe.Maybe String , dataSourceName : Nexosis.Types.DataSet.DataSetName , columns : List Nexosis.Types.Columns.ColumnMetadata , missingValues : List String , dates : { startDate : Time.ZonedDateTime.ZonedDateTime , endDate : Time.ZonedDateTime.ZonedDateTime } , eventName : String , resultInterval : Nexosis.Types.Session.ResultInterval }

aliases.name: ModelSessionRequest
aliases.comment:
Details used to build a `Model`. Provided `ColumnMetadata` will override the metadata of a `DataSet`.
`balance` is only used for `Classification`, and `containsAnomalies` is only used for `AnomalyDetection`.
aliases.type: { name : Maybe.Maybe String , dataSourceName : Nexosis.Types.DataSet.DataSetName , columns : List Nexosis.Types.Columns.ColumnMetadata , missingValues : List String , predictionDomain : Nexosis.Types.PredictionDomain.PredictionDomain , balance : Maybe.Maybe Bool , containsAnomalies : Maybe.Maybe Bool }

name: Nexosis.Types.Model
comment:
In this package, `Model` refers to a machine learning `Model`, used to make predictions on new data, rather than the `Model` in The Elm Architecture.

After a `Session` has completed, a `Model` will be available. This `Model` can be used to make predictions by using the <Nexosis.Api.Mdoels> prediction functions.

Refer to our [documentation](https://docs.nexosis.com/guides/sessions) for more information.

@docs ModelData, ModelList, PredictionResult

aliases.name: ModelData
aliases.comment:
ModelData
Representation of a single Model. Returned from the `/models` endpoint called by <Nexosis.Api.Models>.
aliases.type: { modelId : String , sessionId : String , predictionDomain : Nexosis.Types.PredictionDomain.PredictionDomain , dataSourceName : String , columns : List Nexosis.Types.Columns.ColumnMetadata , createdDate : Time.ZonedDateTime.ZonedDateTime , algorithm : Nexosis.Types.Algorithm.Algorithm , modelName : Maybe.Maybe String , lastUsedDate : Maybe.Maybe Time.ZonedDateTime.ZonedDateTime , metrics : Dict.Dict String Float , links : List Nexosis.Types.Link.Link }

aliases.comment: The results returned when calling [`predict`](Nexosis.Api.Models#predict) on a `Model`.

name: Nexosis.Types.Session
comment:
A `Session` is the representation of the long running processing done when building a machine learning model.

New `Sessions` can be requested, and when completed, results can be retrieved, and the generated machine learning `Models` can be called on to make predictions on new data.

Refer to our [documentation on Sessions](https://docs.nexosis.com/guides/sessions) for more information.

@docs SessionData, SessionList, SessionResults, ResultInterval

aliases.name: SessionData
aliases.comment:
This is the information about a specific `Session`. Some values may not be available until the
`Session` has completed successfully.

aliases.type: { items : List Nexosis.Types.Session.SessionData , pageNumber : Int , totalPages : Int , pageSize : Int , totalCount : Int }

aliases.name: SessionResults
aliases.comment: The results of a Session. The information returned will vary based on the type of `Session` that was run.
aliases.type: { metrics : Dict.Dict String Float , data : List (Dict.Dict String String) }

types.comment: The `DataType` of the data in this column. This determines how the machine learning algorithms will process the data.

types.name: DistributionShape
types.comment: A distribution is calculated for a column, and could be either bucketed `Counts` of values, or `Ranges`.

types.name: Role
types.comment:
The `Role` of the column. `Features` will be used by the machine learning algorithms in calculations,
one column should be designated as the `Target`, which is what the algorithms will try to predict. `None` will
exclude the column from the dataset. `Timestamp` and `Key` are used as unique identifiers for the row of data.

name: Nexosis
comment:
Api Client for use with the [Nexosis Machine Learning Api](https://nexosis.com/). This package provides all of the Api endpoints and types for the request parameters
and response results.


# Configuration

In order to make calls to the Api, you will need an Api key, which you will find on your [Nexosis account](https://account.nexosis.com).

@docs createConfigWithApiKey, ClientConfig


# Advanced Configuration

Provides some more advanced config options, but these will not be needed for most cases.

@docs createConfigWithToken, createConfigWithApiKeyOptions, createConfigWithTokenOptions


# Helpers

These are helpers mostly used within this package, and will probably not need to be used outside of it.

@docs getBaseUrl, withAuthorization, withAppHeader

types.name: ClientConfig
types.comment: Type that holds configuration information that is required to call the Api. This should be carried around on in your model.

values.name: createConfigWithApiKey
values.comment: Create a [`ClientConfig`](#ClientConfig) using only an Api key. Your Api key can be found on your [Nexosis account](https://account.nexosis.com).

values.name: createConfigWithApiKeyOptions
values.comment: Create a config with an Api key, specifying all available options.
values.type: { apiKey : String , baseUrl : String , applicationName : Maybe.Maybe String } -> Nexosis.ClientConfig

values.name: createConfigWithToken
values.comment: Create a [`ClientConfig`](#ClientConfig) using only an Access Token.

values.name: createConfigWithTokenOptions
values.comment: Create a config with token authorization, specifying all available options.
values.type: { token : String , baseUrl : String , applicationName : Maybe.Maybe String } -> Nexosis.ClientConfig

values.name: getBaseUrl
values.comment: Gets the base url that requests will be sent to.

values.name: withAppHeader
values.comment: Adds an application-name header, to help us distinguish where api calls are coming from

values.name: withAuthorization
values.comment: Adds auth headers to an HttpBuilder pipeline
